<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Romania Unhappy about Referee's Time-keeping </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Coach Emerich Jenei of Romania
was unhappy about the extended injury time which allowed Portugal
to a 1-0 win in Arhnem, the Netherlands in Saturday's Euro 2000
group A match.
</P>
<P>
"It is unfortunate that we lost in the last second -- maybe
even after the last second. The referee showed four minutes but
play went on longer than that," Jenei was quoted as saying by a
report.
</P>
<P>
Fourth official Michel Piraux of Belgium indicated there were
four minutes of injury time at the end of the second half. But
UEFA statistics at the end of the match showed the goal was scored
five minutes and 42 seconds after the final whistle, reports said.
</P>
<P>
Asked if he planned to enter a complaint about French referee
Gilles Veissiere, he said. "No, I'm only concerned with our
mistakes. It was a Romanian mistake in defence."
</P>
<P>
Portuguese coach Humberto Coelho was unrepentant.
</P>
<P>
"We played on for a minute after the goal, but I think it's
finished when the referee says it's finished."
</P>
<P>
In a qualifying game for this competition in October 1998, the
boot was on the other foot when Romania, reduced to 10 men,
grabbed a 1-0 victory from Portugal in the dying seconds. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000618.0002 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Singapore Suspends Panadol Capsules Imports From Australia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Singapore has voluntarily
suspended imports of Panadol capsules following a recent attempt
by extortionists in Australia to contaminate the products with
strychnine, the Singaporean Ministry of Health said in a press
releases Saturday.
</P>
<P>
But the ministry said there is no contamination in Singapore,
as it has sampled and tested batches of Panadol capsules imported
from Australia.
</P>
<P>
The local Panadol distributor -- Smith Kline Beecham (S) Pte
Ltd (SKB)-- has confirmed that the contamination occurred at the
point of sale in Australia and has assured the ministry that no
Panadol capsules from Australia are affected.
</P>
<P>
The ministry added that it has been working closely with SKB
as well as its counterpart in Australia to monitor the situation
and ascertain the safety of Panadol products in Singapore.
</P>
</TEXT>
