<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pakistan Not to Respond to Indian Missile Test </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan on Saturday said India
had not given prior information to it about the reported testing
of Prithvi missile on Friday.
</P>
<P>
"No advance notice was given to Pakistan," the Associated Press
of Pakistan (APP) reported quoting the Foreign Office spokesman.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said, according to APP, "as per the understanding
between Pakistan and India, advance warning about the missile
launches are given."
</P>
<P>
He said Pakistan had given advance information when it test
fired its own missiles.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan "has no intention to respond to the Indian missile
test," he added.
</P>
<P>
However, he said, Pakistan is "fully prepared to meet any
external threat or aggression." 
</P>
</TEXT>
