<HEADLINE> Prinosil to Meet Krajicek in Halle Men's Tennis Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, June 17 (Xinhua) -- German David Prinosil and Richard
Krajicek of the Netherlands will meet each other in Sunday's final
of the Halle grass court men's tennis tournament in Halle, Germany.
</P>
<P>
Prinosil scored a 6-4, 7-6 victory over top seed Yevgeny
Kafelnikov of Russia in a semifinal on Saturday while Krajicek
thrashed a listless American Michael Chang 6-2, 6-1 in the other.
</P>
<P>
Prinosil came from 4-2 down in the second set to force a
tiebreak and eventually sealed the victory with a volley which hit
the line.
</P>
<P>
Krajicek said his match against Chang that "I thought it was
going to be more like yesterday...I didn't expect 6-2 6-1."
</P>
<P>
"He was trying to serve to my body but I was able to turn away
and hit with my forehand," he said. "Sometimes it seemed like he
didn't know what to do." 
</P>
</TEXT>
