<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Portugal Beats Romania 1-0 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
BRUSSELS, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Substitute Costinha's head goal
in the fourth minute of injury time gave Portugal a 1-0 victory
over Romania and sent it to the quarterfinals of Euro 2000 on
Saturday at the Gelredome stadium in eastern Dutch town.
</P>
<P>
The two teams, who both favour a patient, passing style,
cancelled each other out until the final seconds of a group A game
played out in midfield and lacking in goalmouth incident, reports
said.
</P>
<P>
Costinha, who had been on the pitch only six minutes, beat the
Romanian defence to a Luis Figo free kick to head his first goal
for his country in only his third appearance.
</P>
<P>
The goal sent the tens of thousands of Portuguese fans
ecstatic and left the Romanians stunned and helpless.
</P>
<P>
"It was a good game. A game of patience, a very tactical game,
" said Portugal's coach Humberto Coelho. "Romania was a very hard
team to beat. It is a difficult team with very experienced players.
</P>
<P>
"It was a tactical game which required a lot of patience but I
think there was justice in the end. I think scoring in the last
minute of a tactical game was phenomenal so now we can look ahead,
" he said.
</P>
<P>
After thrilling the tournament with its dramatic defeat of
England, Portugal looked as if it would have to settle for a 0-0
draw.
</P>
<P>
Portugal set the European Championship alight Monday when Figo,
Rui Costa and Joao Pinto dazzled England to turn a 2-0 deficit
into a famous 3-2 win.
</P>
<P>
Romania drew 1-1 against Germany in its opener.
</P>
<P>
England and Germany played in Charleroi, Belgium, late on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
In front of some 22,000 fans in the eastern Dutch town,
Portugal went forward from the start and in the fifth minute Nuno
Gomes sent a low drive wide of the goal while, three minute later,
defender Fernando Couto tried a blast from just outside the box.
</P>
<P>
But Portugal was not given half the room the English side had
allowed it in the opening match, with the Romanian defense and
midfield fighting fiercely for every ball and committing fouls
whenever necessary.
</P>
<P>
By midway through the first half the game was giving signs
that it was going to be a long slog. By the 22nd minute, Romania
had three yellow cards including one for star player Hagi which
axes him from the side's final game against England.
</P>
<P>
Portugal's star Luis Figo, also got sanctioned in the 30th
minute for shirt pulling.
</P>
<P>
But while Figo could be seen one minute on the right, the next
on the left, back and then forward, Galatasaray's veteran Hagi
stayed on the right using minimum energy.
</P>
<P>
After 60 minutes he looked spent although coach Emerich Jenei
let him ride the full 90 minutes.
</P>
<P>
In the 86th minute Hagi had the best chance for Romania,
forcing Vitor Baia into a superb save from a dipping 20-meter shot.
</P>
<P>
Veissiere signalled four minutes of injury time after a game
full of crunching tackles and in the dying moments Figo whipped a
free kick in from the left of the area and midfielder Costinha
headed home from six meters. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
