<HEADLINE> Egypt, Italy Sign Agreement on Security Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Egypt and Italy signed an agreement
here Sunday aimed at bolstering cooperation in fighting terrorism
and organized crime, Egyptian Interior Minister Habib el-Adli said.
</P>
<P>
The deal, which he signed together with Italian counterpart Enzo
Biancho, pledged joint efforts, including sharing information, in
fighting against terrorism and organized crime, especially money
laundering and illegal immigration.
</P>
<P>
El-Adli told a press conference after meeting with Biancho that
the two sides have agreed to enhance coordination and cooperation
in the fields of security.
</P>
<P>
Biancho said the two countries enjoyed excellent cooperation in
the areas of security and legal immigration. The Egyptian community
in Italy is estimated at 30,000 people, who are perfectly
integrated into the Italian society, he said.
</P>
<P>
He also recalled the importance of tourism in ties between the
two countries, saying that 700,000 Italian tourists visited Egypt
in 1999.
</P>
<P>
The Italian minister arrived here Saturday evening on a three-
day visit. 
</P>
