<HEADLINE> Yemeni President Urges to Combat Corruption </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANAA, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Yemeni President Ali Abdullah Saleh
here Sunday urged for a campaign to combat corruption.
</P>
<P>
During a meeting with senior military and security officials,
Saleh said the anti-corruption campaign is the task of the coming
period.
</P>
<P>
He identified as the main tasks combating corruption in public
institutions, curbing nepotism, and enhancing the rule of law, the
official SABA news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
He also urged for stabilizing security situation in the society,
and toughening punishment against law-breakers, who harm the
country's security and tarnish its image through sabotage acts such
as kidnapping, robbery and other criminal acts.
</P>
<P>
Yemen witnessed a series of kidnappings and robberies against
foreigners in the recent past. Its troops are still searching for
an Italian archaeologist, who was reportedly kidnapped by a tribal
group.
</P>
<P>
"The law-breakers should never be overlooked or tolerated," he
said. "Rather, they should be regarded as a bad example and
severely punished according to the laws and justice." 
</P>
