<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Syria's Ruling Baathist Party Continues National Congress </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Syria's ruling Arab Socialist
Baathist Party (ASBP) continued its ninth national congress here
Sunday morning to hear the reports of the political, organizational
and economic committees.
</P>
<P>
The last national congress was held 15 years ago under late
secretary general of the ASBP and head of state Hafez al-Assad who
ruled Syria for 30 years.
</P>
<P>
The current congress is expected to elect Bashar al-Assad new
ASBP secretary general, 90 new members of the Central Committee and
21 members of the National Leadership to express the desire of the
party to inject new blood to its leadership and introduce Syria to
the 21st century as a strong and skilled country.
</P>
<P>
The tendency to inject new blood to the party leadership does
not necessarily mean the sacrifice of the experienced old-aged
members, according to Syrian sources.
</P>
<P>
The sources expect that the national leadership will include a
number of people who enjoy Bashar's trust such as Prime Minister
Mohammed Mustafa Miro, Foreign Minister Faruk Shareh, Commander of
the Syrian forces in Lebanon General Ebrahim al-Safi, and Deputy
Chief of General Staff General Abdul-Rahman al-Saiyad.
</P>
<P>
Minister of Defense Mohammed Mustafa Tallas, vice president of
the country and ASBP assistant secretary general Abdul Halim
Khaddam, and ASBP assistant general secretaries Suleiman Kaddah and
Abdullah Lahmar will retain their positions in the new national
leadership of the party, the sources added.
</P>
<P>
Earlier on Sunday the ASBP political committee convened under
the chairmanship of Khaddam and with the participation of Lahmar,
who is also chairman of the congress, the Arab-Syrian News Agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
The committee meeting focused on domestic and Arab situations.
It underscored the importance of Arab joint action and unification
of the Arab ranks in the face of risks and challenges posed by the
economic globalization.
</P>
<P>
On the domestic situation, the meeting highlighted the
importance of dealing with the negative aspects in the society,
fostering the sense of responsibility, and stressed the principles
of the rule of law.
</P>
<P>
The organizational and economic committees of the congress also
resumed their functions on Sunday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
