<HEADLINE> Ethiopian Freight Train Hit by Mine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, June 18 (Xinhua) -- A freight transport train that
was going from Addis Ababa to Awash, about 200 km east of the
Ethiopian capital city, was hit by a landmine Saturday morning,
local daily Addis Zemen reported on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The railway authority was quoted as saying that no damage was
caused to the freight or to personnel, except for minor damage to
the rail.
</P>
<P>
Police are doing investigations into the incident, which took
place near Nazereth town, the authority said.
</P>
<P>
The latest bomb accident is the third of its kind on the
Ethio-Djibouti railway since last August.
</P>
<P>
On August 21, 1999, a passenger train from Addis Ababa to the
Port of Djibouti derailed when a bomb exploded, injuring the
driver and his assistant.
</P>
<P>
November 13 of the year also saw two people killed and one
seriously injured in a bomb blast in a passenger train going from
the Ethiopian second largest city Dire Dawa to Addis Ababa.
</P>
</TEXT>
