<HEADLINE> Beijing Law Hotline Receives 200,000 Calls </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 18 (Xinhua) -- A legal services hotline which
opened here June 1 last year, has received 200,000 calls so far,
according to an official source.
</P>
<P>
The hotline, the number of which is 1600148, was opened to
provide legal consultations to the public by the justice
department. In the one year of its existence it has offered law
consultation to more than 70,000 callers, the source said.
</P>
<P>
In order to serve more people, the source added, staff members
of the hotline also publish a bulletin to spread the information
they collect from the hotline conversations. In addition, they
have opened an Internet homepage to present some typical legal
cases. 
