<HEADLINE> Inspection Tour of Shaanxi Concluded </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Xi'an, June 18 (Xinhua) -- An inspection group composed of
members non-Communist parties, the All-China Federation of
Industry and Commerce and non-party personages today concluded
their eight-day inspection tour of Shaanxi Province.
</P>
<P>
The inspection group, organized by United Front Work Department
of the Communist Party of China Central Committee, heard reports
from the Shaanxi provincial government and the city authorities of
Xi'an and Xianyang on their efforts to develop the vast western
regions of the country.
</P>
<P>
They visited the Northwest China Engineering University, the Xi
'an New and High-tech Industrial Development Zone, the Xi'an
Aircraft Industry Corp., and other enterprises and units.
</P>
<P>
The inspectors, headed by Ding Shisun, vice-chairman of the
National People's Congress Standing Committee and chairman of the
China Democratic League Central Committee, held that Shaanxi has
developed a sound foundation in the aspects of energy, science and
education, tourism and many other sectors, which can serve as a
bridgehead for developing the western parts of the country.
</P>
