<HEADLINE> Shanghai Petrochemical Corp. Starts Phase Four Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 18 (Xinhua) -- the Shanghai Petrochemical Corp.
started its phase four project today in a bid to expand
production capacity.
</P>
<P>
The project, with an investment of 6.5 billion yuan (about 785
million U.S. dollars), is expected to be completed in June 2002.
</P>
<P>
Different from the previous projects, the phase four uses some
patent technologies from abroad, leaving detailed design to
domestic institutions.
</P>
<P>
After refurbishing its production machinery, Shanghai
Petrochemical will produce one-fifth of China's ethylene output,
with an annual capacity of 910,000 tons.
</P>
<P>
It will also be able to turn out 200,000 tons of polypropylene
each year. The company is dependent on imports for this material
at present, according to the company.  
