<HEADLINE> Bright Prospect For Logistics Industry In China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 18 (Xinhua) -- With China's entry into the WTO
approaching, China is facing a big opportunity to develop its
logistics industry, said experts at the "China Logistics 2000"
symposium which ended Friday in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Experts from the World Bank and the Asia Pacific Logistics
Institute said that China's stable open policy, continuous
economic development, potential market, and low-cost labor force
provides an excellent basis for developing China's logistic
industry.
</P>
<P>
Statistics said that the total amount of imports and exports
increased from 20.6 billion US dollars in 1978 to 194.9 billion US
dollars in 1999. China cut its tariff to 17 percent last year and
did trade business with 227 countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
Modern logistics is made up of different sectors such as
booking, transportation, storage, processing, and distribution.
China needs to make all the sectors connected to become a network,
said experts.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
