<HEADLINE> Six Billion Yuan to Shelter Beijing from Sandstorms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 18 (Xinhua) -- More than six billion yuan will be
used in the next ten years to protect the Chinese capital from
sandstorms, according to the State Forestry Administration.
</P>
<P>
The government will put the protection of Beijing as its top
priority in its battle against sandstorms and desertification. The
protected zone will cover an area of 260,000 sq km, involving 84
counties around Beijing and neighboring cities.
</P>
<P>
A total of 4.3 million ha will be afforested and protected in
this region, according to the state's plan.
</P>
<P>
Sandstorms have battered Beijing frequently this year, hitting
the city 11 times between March and April.
</P>
<P>
Scientists blame the worsening situation on the increasing
desertification in northern China. 
</P>
