<HEADLINE> Thai Fast-food Challenges Int'l Giants (2) by Yang Qingchuan, Huang Yong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The "brand name effect" is equally important in the Chester's
success story, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Out of such consideration, the name "the Chester's" was
intentionally created to be easily read and remembered by
customers, after repeated consultations with many company image
experts, he recalled.
</P>
<P>
A unique food style is the third important factor, Adirek said.
</P>
<P>
"With the western style fast food becoming a fashion in
Thailand today, the customers, especially teenagers, have already
adopted the style. So we decided to mix the Thai and western
styles in our fast food, thus making an special attraction."
</P>
<P>
The grilled chicken, which is the Chester's brand food, can be
seen as a kind of typical Thai-western mixture, with western ways
of grilling and Thai spices combined together, he said.
</P>
<P>
"This kind of style is more suitable for the Thai people, and
is welcomed by more and more customers," he noted.
</P>
<P>
The last factor for success, Adirek stated, is the adoption of
the international standards.
</P>
<P>
"During more than a decade of experience of running fast-food
business, I realized that if we want to compete with international
big chain stores, we should keep improving our production,
management, service and everything else to meet international
standards," he said.
</P>
<P>
Strict training for employees, imposing same food production
standards in every branches, creating a modern inside-store
environment and initiating a quick delivery service, are all the
efforts the Thai fast-food business makes to keep up to the
international level, he remarked.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, he said, for keeping confidence and a high
profile, the Chester's mainly focuses on the big cities.
</P>
<P>
"We know the competition in big cities is intense, but we
resolve to learn from competition, and grow up through competition,
" a smiling Adirek said, hinting the company is now considering
exploring overseas markets, to take on the giants on the
international battlefield.
</P>
<P>
The CP success story has also inspired other Thai fast-food
stores to emerge, for the moment, the S&AMP;P and M&AMP;K.
</P>
<P>
Asked about the group's prospect, he stressed, "we are both
confident and realistic. we know we still have a long way to go,
but we see the hope and we will carry on our efforts." 
</P>
