<HEADLINE> Beijing Launches Digital Community </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Digital community became a reality
today as residents moved into Beijing's Huilongguan Residential
Quarter and started to enjoy digital service.
</P>
<P>
Every household is entitled to access the website of the
digital community, where they may inquire about charges collected,
request various community services, chat with other residents, and
shop in the virtual supermarket.
</P>
<P>
The digital community greatly improves the efficiency of
property management and makes the communication between the
residents and the property managers more convenient and smooth,
according to residents in the Huilongguan Residential Quarter.
</P>
<P>
Located in the suburban Changping District in Beijing, the
Huilongguan Residential Quarter is designed as the biggest
residential quarter for economic housing owners. With a projected
living space of 8.5 million square meters, the quarter is expected
to provide housing for nearly 300,000 residents. The first phase
of the housing project for about 6,000 households has been
completed. 
