<HEADLINE> China's Leading Petrochemical Giant Starts Fourth Phase Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai Petrochemical Company
Limited, China's leading petrochemical producer, started its
fourth phase construction today with the investment of 6.5 billion
yuan.
</P>
<P>
When the expansion project is completed in June of 2002, the
company is expected to process 10 million tons of crude oil and
produce up to one million tons of ethylene and other synthetic
fiber materials annually.
</P>
<P>
The fourth phase construction of the petrochemical giant
includes the technological upgrading of facilities with an annual
production capacity of 700,000 ton of ethylene and the
construction of new facilities with an annual production capacity
of 250,000 tons of polyethylene as well as 200,000 tons of
polypropylene.
</P>
<P>
When the projects are completed, the company can produce 910,
000 tons of ethylene, one-fifth of the country's total. 
</P>
