<DOCNO> XIE20000618.0118 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> More Educational Spending for Beijing Children </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 18 (Xinhua) -- The average expenditure on a child
's education per household in Beijing was 3,860 yuan (465 U.S.
dollars) last year, higher than the average level spent elsewhere
in China, according to the Beijing Municipal Statistics Bureau.
</P>
<P>
Experts attributed the higher level of educational spending to
the importance citizens attach to education, the relatively high
income and the high cost of educational expenses in general.
</P>
<P>
The average expenditure of a college student in the Chinese
capital was 9,428 yuan (1,136 U.S. dollars) with tuition and board
costing the most.
</P>
<P>
Parents of primary and senior high school students spend a
great deal of money to allow their children to study playing
musical instruments, painting, computers, sports and science.
Costs for these services are increasing.
</P>
<P>
In addition, parents are willing to pay more for private
instructors.
</P>
<P>
According to the bureau, children in Beijing are required to
attend a specified school, which is usually located near their
homes. However, some parents want their children to go to other
schools that have higher-quality teachers and better equipment.
Families have to pay a large amount of money to the alternative
schools before a child can be admitted. 
</P>
</TEXT>
