<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 110 Bridges Built in Myanmar in 12 Years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar has built a total of 110
bridges in the country since 1988, spreading in 13 states and
divisions, official newspaper The New Light of Myanmar reported
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The over-60-meter-long bridges, built by the Myanmar Ministry
of Construction, include 28 in Ayeyawaddy division, 19 in Rakhine
state, 16 in Yangon division, 8 in Bago division, 7 each in Magway
division and kachin state, 6 in Sagaing division and 5 in Shan
state, Third Secretary of the Myanmar State Peace and Development
Council Lieutenant-General Win Myint was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
The 110 bridges also include 8 river-crossing bridges -- four
crossing the Ayeyawaddy river, three crossing the Thanlwin river
and one crossing the Chindwin river.
</P>
<P>
Besides, the ministry has also built 6916.8 kilometers (km) of
roads since 1988 with its total length extended to 30,232.8 km,
the report said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Myanmar has designated 80 roads with a total length
of 24,659 km as the country's union highways, up from 11 in the
past with a total length of 3,923 km.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar has laid down plans systematically for better
transportation, building bridges and roads in the country in its
bid to uplift socio-economic life of local people and development
of the nation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
