<HEADLINE> Strong Earthquake Hit Iceland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, June 17 (Xinhua) -- A strong earthquake hit Iceland
on Saturday as it celebrated National Day, but fortunately no
death is reported.
</P>
<P>
The quake, which struck at 3:41 in the afternoon (15:41 GMT),
was centered in the Holt region, near Mount Hekla, 88 Kilometers
southeast of the capital Reykjavik. It measured between 6.5 and 6.
6 on the Richter scale, according to the Icelandic Meteorological
Society.
</P>
<P>
The quake was felt all over the country. Fortunately, nobody
was hurt since Saturday was the country's national day and most
people were outdoors spending the holiday in beautiful weather
when the quake hit, the Iceland Radio reported.
</P>
<P>
However, damage to roads and houses were reported, the radio
said. 
</P>
