<HEADLINE> Weekly Review of Regional News In China (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 18 (Xinhua) -- The following is a weekly review
of major regional news in China from 11 to 17 in June.
</P>
<P>
BEIJING: China's first website on TV program trade and TV
advertisement information will start operation in July. The
website, TV-trade.net, has so far reached intents of agreements
with about 500 TV stations, TV program producers and advertising
companies from both home and abroad.
</P>
<P>
An earthquake measuring 6.8 on the Richter scale rocked central
Taiwan at 02:23 (Beijing time) on June 11. The quake was felt all
over the island, with the epicenter at the county of Nantou,
according to the State Seismological Bureau in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
A virtual reality theater is to be built within the Forbidden
City to showcase the country's centuries-old architecture and
cultural relics, according to a letter of intent signed recently
in Beijing between the Palace Museum and Japan's Toppan Printing
Co. ltd.
</P>
<P>
The Fifth National Survey on China's Forest Resources indicates
that the acreage of the country's man-made forest exceeds 46
million hectares, ranking first in the world.
</P>
<P>
The "21st Century Forum -- Conference 2000", sponsored by the
National Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference, China's top advisory body, concluded in Beijing on
June 16. The theme of the three-day forum is economic
globalization -- Asia and China.
</P>
</TEXT>
