<HEADLINE> China To Build Museum On Medicine Resources </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUIYANG, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Southwest China's Guizhou province
plans to build a museum on medicine resources in Guiyang, the
province's capital, according to the provincial health department.
</P>
<P>
The museum will have nine exhibition halls covering 6,170
square meters and will mainly exhibit traditional Chinese medicine.
The museum will also collect and exhibit traditional medicines
from various ethnic groups in China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
