<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Weekly Review of Education News in China (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The new Jilin University was set up in northeast China's Jilin
Province on June 12 merging with four other universities.
</P>
<P>
The new university was set up by merging Jilin University,
Jilin Polytechnical University, Changchun Science and Technology
University, Changchun Post and Telecommunication University, and
Dr. Norman Bethune Medical University.
</P>
<P>
The university has more than 39,000 students and 15,600 faculty
members. It offers 130 undergraduate courses, 180 masters degrees
and 71 Ph.D. courses
</P>
<P>
Art Education Base for Children Established
</P>
<P>
An art education base for children was set up on June 12 in Xi'
an, capital of northwest China's Shaanxi Province, in a bid to
foster children's environmental awareness.
</P>
<P>
The base, established by the International Fund for China's
Environment (IFCE) and "Little Swan Art Troupe", calls on people
from all walks of life to take care of the environment and promote
and develop a harmonious living style.
</P>
<P>
 Qinghua University Receives Donation from Hong Kong
Entrepreneur
</P>
<P>
Qinghua University, one of China's most prestigious
universities, received 50 million yuan (about six million U.S.
dollars) from a Hong Kong entrepreneur Chao Kuang-piu on June 12.
</P>
<P>
An official from the university said that the donation will be
used for the construction of a Sports Center, which will be the
largest indoor sports center ever constructed at Qinghua since it
was founded almost ninety years ago. The center, with total
investment of 84 million yuan (about ten million U.S. dollars),
will become an important landmark at the University.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
