<HEADLINE> Weekly Review of Education News in China (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 18 (Xinhua) -- The following is a review of major
education news released by Xinhua from June 11 to June 17:
</P>
<P>
 China's First Job-Seeking Website for Graduates
</P>
<P>
The opening of China's first job-seeking website --www.9989.net-
- will make it easier for Chinese university graduates to get over
the difficulties.
</P>
<P>
The website, founded by some postgraduates from Nanjing
University aims to collect and provide information for local
university graduates and employers.
</P>
<P>
China to Promote Distance Education in Western Regions
</P>
<P>
China is to spend 360 million yuan (43 million US dollars) on
developing distance education in its western part, according to an
official from the Ministry of Education.
</P>
<P>
Wang Zhuzhu, deputy director of the ministry's tele-education
office, said the investment constitutes a major move by the state
to develop education in the economically backward western regions.
</P>
<P>
 Science, Education Top Priority for China's Western
Development: Li
</P>
<P>
Chinese Vice-Premier Li Lanqing stressed the importance of
science, technology and education reforms in developing western
China on June 12.
</P>
<P>
Li said further educational reforms are needed to produce all
kinds of professionals for the ongoing massive development in
China's west.
</P>
</TEXT>
