<HEADLINE> Malchow Sets 200-meter Butterfly Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 17 (Xinhua) -- American Tom Malchow on
Saturday set a world record in the 200-meter butterfly in
Charlotte, North Carolina, beating the mark set by Denis Pankratov
of Russia in 1995.
</P>
<P>
Malchow clocked 1 minute, 55:18 seconds in the Charlotte
UltraSwim, topping Pankratov's mark of 1 minute, 55:22 seconds.
</P>
