<HEADLINE> What's on Weekly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 18 (Xinhua) -- This week's concerts will both
start and end with romantic and sentimental music.
</P>
<P>
China Opera and Ballet Traditional Music Ensemble will give a
concert featuring traditional Chinese music this evening at the
Beijing Concert Hall.
</P>
<P>
The programs will include some very familiar music, such as "
Liang Shanbo and Zhu Yingtai", known as the Chinese version of
Romeo and Juliet, and the Jasmine.
</P>
<P>
The concert hall will give the stage to a choral concert on
Tuesday evening. Audience will be able to listen to some western
China folk songs composed or collected by Wang Luobin, a famous
Chinese musician.
</P>
<P>
The Stairway to Music 2000 Afternoon Concerts series will
present a piano duo and four hands with a dynamic name of "Dancing
on the Keyboard" at 14:00 on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Music from the original version of Romeo and Juliet will be
played in the evening at a concert on prime music from Hollywood
movies and classical lyric from Broadway. Other music includes
selections from Gone with the Wind, Out of Africa, Dancing with
the Wolf, and Saving Private Ryan.
</P>
<P>
China Film Orchestra will play the concert with conductor Li
Ling. 
</P>
</TEXT>
